[The 2 additional cases mentioned on the End Polio Pakistan website during this week have not as yet been included in the weekly global update. That being said, the global tally of WPV1 cases confirmed since 1 Jan 2019 is now at 18 - 7 in Afghanistan and 11 in Pakistan. The report of additional positive environmental samples in Pakistan, including in areas not recently confirming actual cases serves as confirming continued circulation of the WPV1 in the country.

While there have not been cases of cVDPV confirmed in the past week, the isolation of a cVDPV2 from a healthy contact in Niger confirms the continued circulation of the cVDPV in Niger, as well as in Kwara state Nigeria where there was a positive environmental sample.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

