[3] Pakistan (KPTD) - media report
Date: Thu 9 May 2019
Source: Dunya News [edited]
https://dunyanews.tv/en/Pakistan/490714-New-polio-case-surfaces-in-North-Waziristan


A new polio case surfaced in tribal district of North Waziristan in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, raising the tally of polio cases to 13 across the country in the current year [2019], Dunya News reported on [Wed 8 May 2019]. According to Emergency Operation Centre, polio virus has been confirmed in a 3-year-old girl in North Waziristan.

Polio is a highly infectious disease that invades the nervous system and can cause irreversible paralysis in a matter of hours. It is now endemic in only 2 countries, Pakistan and Afghanistan [Nigeria has not as yet been declared polio free, with the date of onset of last WPV1 associated disease having been on 21 Aug 2016. - Mod.MPP]

Efforts to eliminate polio in Pakistan have became complicated in recent years, as polio workers have faced attacks by militants who say the health teams are Western spies, or that the vaccines they administer are intended to sterilize children.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This report mentions the gender of the case. - Mod.MPP]

******
[4] Pakistan, outcome April 2019 campaign - media report
Date: Thu 9 May 2019, 10:18 PM
Source: Urdu Point News [edited]
https://www.urdupoint.com/en/health/95-target-achieved-in-recent-polio-eradicati-617694.html


Parliamentary Secretary for National Health Services, Regulations and Coordination Dr. Nausheen Hamid has said that 95% coverage as well as target was achieved during the polio eradication campaign in April 2019. She stated this while responding to a Calling Attention Notice regarding increase in the number of polio cases in the country due to rise in refusal rate to administer polio vaccine to children.

She said that effective immunization campaigns are the only way to eradicate polio virus from the country. She said polio vaccination campaigns are launched to fully eradicate the disease from Pakistan. She added that a special campaign was launched in April [2019], while the similar initiative would be launched in next July [2019].

According to Dr. Nausheen Hamid, poliovirus continues to exist in sewage water in Pakistan causing eruption of this disease in various parts of the country. She said that unfortunately, some elements create hurdles in the way of effective polio eradication campaigns, adding that an exclusive social media cell has been established at her ministry to create awareness against polio.

Earlier, the Minister of State for Parliamentary Affairs responded to another Calling Attention Notice regarding poor performance of cell phone towers in the country due to non-maintenance or service.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Note that the nationwide polio vaccination campaign was held in the latter part of April 2019, and the recent cases (including the 2 additional cases not as yet mentioned in the weekly GPEI updates) all had dates of onset on or before this vaccination campaign. Time will tell if the 95% coverage was sufficient to interrupt transmission of the WPV1 in Pakistan. It would be very unfortunate if the 5% estimated to have been missed in this latest campaign were clustered in close proximity, thereby presenting pockets of susceptibles that could support continued circulation of the wild poliovirus. - Mod.MPP]
